torms our hero encountered. Additionally, the actors seamlessly moved from background roles to prominent characters in Rougemont’s self-told story.\r\n\r\n<em>Shipwrecked!</em> is a family-oriented play that glorifies the high points of a man’s extravagant—almost crass—adventure within the elitist Victorian era. This 90-minute, one-act play easily accommodates quick scene changes and a wide array of different personas—watch carefully, even Queen Victoria makes an appearance.\r\n\r\nShipwrecked! <em>will run at 7:30 p.m. with matinees at 2 p.m. through Dec. 19 in PlayMakers’ Paul Green Theatre at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. Tickets are available for purchase at </em><a href="http://www.playmakersrep.org"><em>www.playmakersrep.org</em></a><em>.</em>\r\n\r\n<em> </em>', 'Review: Shipwrecked! @ PlayMakers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '302-revision-2', '', '', '2010-12-07 04:10:35', '2010-12-07 04:10:35', '', 302, 'http://recess.nujigroup.com/?p=305', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
