or Mini-Series goes to Chris Colfer, playing Kurt from <em>Glee</em>, starting off what could be another big night for the show on the right foot.\r\n\r\n8:18 Best Mini-Series or TV Movie goes to<em> Carlos</em>, which is a bit of a surprise, with the industry favorite and Critics'' Choice winner being<em> The Pacific.</em>\r\n\r\n8:10 Best TV Performance by an Actress goes to Katey Sagal from <em>Sons of Anarchy.</em> They cut off her speech oh so quickly.  Blame it on Christian Bale.\r\n\r\n8:07 - Christian Bale takes home the Best Supporting Actor award, and deservedly so.  His transformation into Dickie was absolutely incredible.  But he really needs to take on roles of a more consistent body weight.\r\n\r\n8:04 - Ricky Gervais is already offending people, targeting perhaps the two worst nominations of the year, <em>Burlesque</em> and<em> The Tourist</em>.  He also makes fun of Scientologists and gets a big "ooooh" from the audience.  Get over yourselves.', 'The 68th Annual Golden Globe Awards - Live Blog', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '462-revision-51', '', '', '2011-01-17 03:22:38', '2011-01-17 03:22:38', '', 462, 'http://recess.nujigroup.com/?p=531', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
